---
title: Vegan Asparagus & Golden Rice Bowls with Peas, Red Onion & Pistachio-Parsley Chimichurri
description: This loaded vegan rice bowl is one hearty flavor bomb of a meal! You’ll whip up a bed of fluffy golden turmeric rice with chewy golden raisins, then top it with a vibrant, garlicky mix of sautéed asparagus, red onion, and sweet peas. It’s all drizzled with a zingy, herbaceous homemade pistachio and parsley chimichurri that complements the whole dish beautifully.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/65423ed1d4ae2bce30667dbc-dffbb313.jpeg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/65423ed1d4ae2bce30667dbc.pdf
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/vegan-asparagus-golden-rice-bowls-65423ed1d4ae2bce30667dbc
author: HelloFresh
servings: 2
time required: 25 minutes
cuisine: North America
nutrition:
  calories: 670 kcal
  fat: 26 g
  saturated fat: 3.5 g
  carbohydrates: 94 g
  sugar: 19 g
  protein: 12 g
  fiber: 7 g
  sodium: 200 mg
course: main course
---

Wash and dry produce.

Peel and mince @garlic{2%cloves}.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{2%tsp} in a #small pot{} over medium-high heat. Add half the minced garlic and @turmeric{1%tsp} (all the turmeric for 4 servings). Cook, stirring constantly, until fragrant, ~{30-60%seconds}.

Add @jasmine rice{3/4%cup}, @veggie stock concentrate{1}, @water{1 1/4%cups} (2¼ cups for 4), and a pinch of @salt{}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until tender, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

While rice cooks, mince @parsley{1/4%oz}. Roughly chop @pistachios{1/2%oz}. Trim and discard woody bottom ends from @asparagus{6%oz}; cut crosswise into 1-inch pieces. Halve, peel, and thinly slice half the @red onion{1} (whole onion for 4 servings).

In a #small bowl{}, combine parsley, pistachios, @garlic powder{1%tsp}, @olive oil{2 1/2%tbsp}, @red wine vinegar{1%tsp}, @salt{}, and @pepper{} (5 TBSP olive oil and 2 tsp vinegar for 4).

> TIP: Add a little more vinegar if you prefer a tangier chimichurri.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add asparagus and sliced onion; season with salt and pepper. Cook, stirring, until lightly browned and tender, ~{3-5%minutes}.

In the last minute of cooking, stir in @peas{4%oz} and remaining minced garlic. Cook, stirring occasionally, until garlic is fragrant and peas are warmed through.

Fluff rice with a #fork{}; stir in @golden raisins{1%oz}.

Divide rice between shallow bowls and top with veggies. Drizzle chimichurri over top. Serve.